### Q7: What is the difference between `drop_duplicates()` strategies?
**A:**
```python
# Keep first occurrence (default)
df.drop_duplicates(keep="first", inplace=True)

# Keep last occurrence
df.drop_duplicates(keep="last", inplace=True)

# Drop ALL copies of any duplicate
df.drop_duplicates(keep=False, inplace=True)

# Duplicate on specific columns only
df.drop_duplicates(subset=["CustomerID","Date","Product"], keep="first")
```
We use the default (`keep="first"`) — reasonable assumption that the first recorded
transaction is the original.

